reference.ref: L.A. Shalabi, Z. Shaaban and B. Kasasbeh. Data Mining: A Preprocessing Engine. Journal of Computer Science 2:9 (2006) 735-739

generalDescription.type: Execution of nominal to binary method to transform the nominal attributes into a set of binary ones. Each value of the original nominal attribute will conform a new binary attribute.
generalDescription.objective: Obtain a data set with transformed data
generalDescription.howWork: Application of a preprocess task by means of creating one new attribute for each value of the original nominal one. The new binary attribute will have a '1' value if the associated nominal value was present in the original instance, '0' otherwise.
